The Chronicle Gwanda Correspondent A 25-YEAR-OLD man from Maphisa is on the run after he allegedly fatally stabbed his neighbour with a knife on the chest over an undisclosed issue. Matabeleland South acting provincial police spokesperson, Sergeant Stanford Mguni confirmed the incident which occurred at Marinoha Business Centre in Maphisa on Sunday at around 9PM. He said Pardon Ndlovu had a fight with Mr Brighton Zimuto on Friday last week and a fellow villager intervened. Sgt Mguni said the pair had another confrontation on Sunday and this time Ndlovu stabbed Mr Zimuto and he died on the spot. More to followâ€¦